.TH SIGRETURN 2 "2025" "Nightingale" "Nightingale System Calls"
.SH NAME
sigreturn \- return from signal handler
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <signal.h>
.PP
.BI "int sigreturn(int " code ");"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sigreturn()
is used to return from a signal handler and restore the execution
context that was interrupted by the signal.
.PP
This system call is typically not called directly by user code.
Instead, it is invoked automatically by the signal trampoline code
when a signal handler function returns.
.PP
.I code
is the return code from the signal handler.
.PP
When called,
.B sigreturn()
restores the saved register state and stack pointer,
allowing execution to continue from the point where the signal was delivered.
.PP
This function does not return normally; it restores the interrupted context.
.SH RETURN VALUE
This function does not return to the caller.
Execution continues from the point where the signal was received.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sigaction (2),
.BR kill (2)
